The side length of the rhombus is $n,$ so its area is \[\frac{1}{2}(n)(n\sqrt{3}) = \frac{n^2\sqrt{3}}{2}.\] The area of each of the two rectangles is \[n\cdot \frac{n}{2} = \frac{n^2}{2},\] so the area of both rectangles is $n^2.$  Therefore, the area of the shaded region is $\frac{n^2\sqrt{3}}{2} - n^2 = \frac{n^2(\sqrt{3}-2)}{2}.$

